Apply 3 changes to frontend/design_system/rockyridgeai-dental.com/ui_kits/website/dashboard.html to upgrade the New Appointment drawer with typeahead search for
 Patient/Provider fields and a New Patient sub-drawer. Read the file first, then apply these changes:

 **Change 1 — CSS** Insert after the `.field-row` rule (line 55), before `/* Toast */`:

 .search-select { position: relative; }
 .search-results { position: absolute; top: 100%; left: 0; right: 0; z-index: 10; background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--rr-parchment); border-radius: 6px; box-shadow:
 var(--shadow-md); margin-top: 4px; max-height: 200px; overflow-y: auto; }
 .search-opt { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; padding: 8px 12px; cursor: pointer; font-family: var(--font-ui); font-size: .88rem; color: var(--rr-ink); }
 .search-opt:hover { background: var(--rr-steel-050); }
 .search-opt.selected { background: var(--rr-steel-100); font-weight: 600; }
 .search-opt .search-sub { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: .7rem; color: var(--rr-slate-dark); margin-left: auto; }
 .search-ava { width: 28px; height: 28px; border-radius: 999px; background: hsl(var(--primary)); color: #fff; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-weight:
 600; font-size: .66rem; flex-shrink: 0; }
 .field-label-row { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; }
 .field-link { font-family: var(--font-ui); font-size: .75rem; color: hsl(var(--primary)); cursor: pointer; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 500; }
 .field-link:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
 .drawer-back { background: none; border: none; cursor: pointer; padding: 6px; color: var(--rr-slate-dark); border-radius: 4px; margin-right: 10px; display: inline-flex; align-items:
 center; }
 .drawer-back:hover { background: var(--rr-off-white); color: var(--rr-ink); }

 **Change 2 — Add PROVIDERS array + NewPatientDrawer component** Insert BEFORE `const NewAppointmentDrawer`:

 const PROVIDERS = [
 { id: 'hau', name: 'Dr Hau Le', op: 'Operatory 1' },
 { id: 'sara', name: 'Dr Sara Lim', op: 'Operatory 2' },
 { id: 'renu', name: 'Hyg. Renu', op: 'Operatory 3' },
 ];

 const NewPatientDrawer = ({ onClose, onSave }) => {
 // Form with fields from Patient schema: first_name, last_name, dob, phone, email, insurance_provider, is_minor, guardian_name, consent_approved
 // Has a back arrow button (drawer-back class) in header that calls onClose
 // On save: generates random P-XXXXX id, pushes to window.PATIENTS, calls onSave(newPatient)
 // Uses same drawer/field/d-input CSS classes as NewAppointmentDrawer
 // Fields: First name*, Last name* (field-row), DOB, Phone + Email (field-row), Insurance provider, is_minor checkbox (conditionally shows guardian_name), consent checkbox
 // Footer: Back (ghost) + Save patient (primary, disabled if no first/last name)
 };

 **Change 3 — Replace NewAppointmentDrawer** to use typeahead search instead of <select> for Patient and Provider:
 - Patient field: has "field-label-row" with label + blue "New patient" link on right. Input is a search-select with typeahead dropdown showing avatar + name + id. Clicking "New
 patient" sets showNewPatient=true which renders NewPatientDrawer instead. On save, auto-selects the new patient and returns to appointment drawer.
 - Provider field: same typeahead pattern filtering PROVIDERS array, showing name + operatory.
 - All other fields (Procedure, Date/Time, Duration, Notes) stay unchanged.
 - State: patient (object|null), patientQ, patientFocus, provider (object|null), providerQ, providerFocus, date, time, showNewPatient
 - if (showNewPatient) return <NewPatientDrawer onClose={()=>setShowNewPatient(false)} onSave={(p)=>{setPatient(p);setPatientQ(p.first+' '+p.last);setShowNewPatient(false);}} />

